WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:02.400
Previously on "Manhattan"...

00:02.433 --> 00:03.900
We're about to have our
very own plutonium factory.

00:04.233 --> 00:08.233
If our colleagues don't wipe the
Confederate states off the face of the Earth.

00:08.933 --> 00:10.766
You leave for Tennessee tomorrow morning.

00:10.800 --> 00:13.633
I just saw Charlie this morning at the gate

00:13.666 --> 00:15.833
with Helen Prins and a mountain of luggage.

00:15.866 --> 00:17.600
Who's Helen Prins?

00:19.100 --> 00:20.366
Hope you're not too lonely.

00:20.400 --> 00:23.033
All by yourself on that business trip.

00:23.066 --> 00:24.566
I should have brought a book.

00:24.600 --> 00:26.633
You've got a busy day, Mr. Ellis.

00:26.666 --> 00:29.100
If it would be helpful, I can
walk our guests through the plant.

00:29.137 --> 00:30.888
Compartmentalization, Theodore.

00:30.939 --> 00:32.974
I don't think Washington would like that.

00:33.008 --> 00:35.059
But I could use some coffee.

00:35.110 --> 00:36.561
It's Private Dunlavey, right?

00:36.612 --> 00:38.863
Don't pretend you know anything about me

00:38.897 --> 00:42.283
just because you put a bullet
through my dad's mathematician.

00:47.155 --> 00:49.290
You know, I've seen you before.

00:53.028 --> 00:56.464
- Music.
- That's right, music.

00:56.498 --> 00:59.417
The reactor will be fully
operational within a day.

00:59.468 --> 01:01.752
We gave you a list of 22 major hazards

01:01.803 --> 01:03.471
to resolve before we go critical.

01:03.505 --> 01:05.256
And the army intends to give your list

01:05.307 --> 01:06.908
the consideration it deserves.

01:06.942 --> 01:09.644
- When?
- Just as soon as we're critical.

